  "title": "TAX AND COMPLIANCE ACCOUNTANT",
  "description": "<p>Responsible for the tax and compliance matters, board meeting affairs and internal controls. Ensuring that all transactions and records conform to Singapore, International tax and other government regulations. The duties assigned will be varied; these will include but not be limited to the following;</p><p><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p><p>Responsible for the tax matters within the group of Companies in Singapore. Including preparation of tax returns for Individual Tax / GST / Withholding Tax.</p><ul><li>Responsible for the corporate secretarial matters for all companies within the Singapore Group of Companies including liaising with service providers on the filing of Annual Returns with ACRA.</li><li>Manages Singapore tax audit and internal audits from Head office in      China.</li><li>Assist with conducting tax research and analysis to ensure tax optimization throughout the organization.</li><li>Maintain all files related to tax and company registration.</li><li>Undertake any other ad-hoc projects/ duties assigned.</li><li>Other duties as required</li></ul><p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENT</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Accountancy or Business Management</li><li>5 years of related work experience.</li><li>Whose experience in an accounting firm or Big MNC will be added advantage.</li><li>Good knowledge of Singapore taxes; personal and GST.</li><li>Strong numerical and analytical skills.</li><li>Independent with minimal supervision in a complex setup and tight timeline.</li><li>Possess strong communication skills and proficiency in both written and spoken languages.</li><li>Experience in transfer pricing and international taxation will be added advantage.</li><li>Experience in corporate secretarial matters preferred.</li><li>MS Office / SAP.</li></ul>",
